Package model

Class Appointment

  • java.lang.Object
    • model.Appointment
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    WithID
    public class Appointment
extends java.lang.Object
implements WithID
    Class representing an appointment, containing information about the appointment from the database or prepared for storage in the database. The class includes a set() method for simultaneously setting all modifiable properties, allowing the class to provide a single error message reporting all problems in the data. The class also implements some derived values for rendering in tables.
    Author:
    Joseph T. Lapp

                   long contactId,
                   ContactCache contactCache)
            throws InvalidArgException
        Constructs an appointment from user-provided information in preparation for storage in the database. The appointment's ID will be given its database-assigned value once it is stored in the database.
        Parameters:
        title - Appointment title
        description - Appointment description
        location - Appointment location
        type - Appointment type
        startTime - Appointment starting time
        endTime - Appointment ending time
        createdBy - Name of user that created the appointment
        customerId - ID of customer having the appointment
        userId - ID of user that created the appointment
        contactId - ID of contact having the appointment
        contactCache - Contacts as cached from the database
        Throws:
        InvalidArgException - when one or more of the provided arguments is invalid, in which case the error message lists all the errors in all of the arguments, delimited by semicolons
